

How to set image file size after using TAR in windows terminal

$fs = [System.IO.File]::Open("Path to image file that was tar'ed", 'Open', 'Write')
$fs.SetLength(1440KB)
$fs.Close()

how to get rid of ^M in MINIX vi

:s%/^M//g
where "^M" is typed by inputing "CTRL+V" and "CRTL+M" in order

Minix partition structure
- while there does exist all 16 partitions in /dev, which are /dev/c0d0p0s0-/dev/c0d0p3s3
  there is only 1 partions and 3 sub partitions that actually exist on the controller image
  so if we want to test giving no partitions, we input /dev/c0d0p0s0, /dev/c0d0p0s1 or /dev/c0d0p0s2


